<%# Phase 26 — 01b. Slack webhook pane.

    Settings pane for the install-level Slack webhook. Submits to
    `PATCH /settings/slack_webhook` (mounted as
    `Settings::SlackWebhooksController#update`). The controller:

      1. Validates the URL against `SLACK_URL_REGEX`.
      2. Fires a test ping via `Webhooks::SlackClient#ping`.
      3. Only persists the row (`notification_delivery_channels`,
         `kind = "slack"`) when the ping returns 2xx.

    The two checkboxes (`everything`, `daily_digest`) cross the wire
    as `"yes"` / `"no"` per CLAUDE.md hard rules. The controller's
    `coerce_boolean` helper flips them back to Boolean for storage.

    The pane reads current state from the AR row (if any). When no
    row exists yet both checkboxes render unchecked and the URL
    field renders empty. %>
<%# 2026-05-16 — Slack webhook saves are plain saves now. The
    recent-TOTP gate that previously fronted this surface (and the
    `totp-modal` Stimulus wiring that opened the verification modal
    on `[update]`) was dropped. The only /settings write that still
    pops the TOTP-code modal is the profile pane. %>
<div class="pane">
  <%= form_with url: settings_slack_webhook_path, method: :patch, local: true do |_f| %>
    <fieldset style="padding: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px; border: none;">
      <legend><h2>Slack</h2></legend>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label for="slack_webhook_url" class="form-label">webhook URL</label>
        <input type="text" name="slack_webhook_url" id="slack_webhook_url"
               value="<%= @slack_webhook&.webhook_url %>"
               placeholder="https://hooks.slack.com/services/T.../B.../..."
               autocomplete="off"
               style="max-width: 420px; width: 100%;">
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label class="md-check">
          <input type="checkbox" name="everything" value="yes"
                 <%= "checked" if @slack_webhook&.everything %>>
          <span class="md-check-indicator"></span>
          <span class="md-check-label">every notification</span>
        </label>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom: 6px;">
        <label class="md-check">
          <input type="checkbox" name="daily_digest" value="yes"
                 <%= "checked" if @slack_webhook&.daily_digest %>>
          <span class="md-check-indicator"></span>
          <span class="md-check-label">daily digest</span>
        </label>
        <span class="form-hint" style="display: block;">sent daily at 09:00 in your time zone.</span>
      </div>

      <%# Unchecked boxes post no value at all; the controller's
          `coerce_boolean` helper treats absence as `false`. This
          matches the existing Voyage pane checkbox pattern. %>

      <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 6px;">
        <button type="submit">[update]</button>
        <%# Phase 26 — 01d. `[help]` link opens the layout-level
            webhook help modal with the Slack guide. The href is the
            full Markdown fragment URL so JS-off users still land on
            a usable page (the controller renders the same fragment
            without a layout, but a direct hit returns HTML readable
            in any browser).

            2026-05-16 polish — rendered through
            BracketedMutedLinkComponent (the muted bracketed-link
            primitive) so `[help]` reads as the secondary affordance
            next to the loud primary `[update]`, matching the
            `[ authorize ] [ cancel ]` hierarchy on the Doorkeeper
            consent page. Plain whitespace separator (the prior
            middle-dot `nav-sep` was dropped in the same pass — the
            visual hierarchy of loud-vs-muted carries the grouping on
            its own). %>
        <%= render(BracketedMutedLinkComponent.new(
              label: "help",
              href: settings_webhooks_help_path(provider: "slack"),
              data: {
                action: "click->webhook-help-modal#open",
                webhook_help_modal_provider_param: "slack"
              }
            )) %>
      </div>
    </fieldset>
  <% end %>
</div>
